49:32.012 --> 49:32.665
Jill!

49:51.597 --> 49:52.685
We're ready, Sarah.

51:05.714 --> 51:06.193
Jill!

51:08.674 --> 51:09.153
Jill!

52:14.087 --> 52:14.522
No!

53:05.486 --> 53:05.921
Jill?

53:32.121 --> 53:35.299
Is this even real?

53:35.429 --> 53:36.300
Does it even matter?

53:42.088 --> 53:45.613
Are you-- is Jill OK?

54:18.603 --> 54:19.081
Sh.

54:22.084 --> 54:22.520
Sh.

55:39.118 --> 55:39.901
How are you feeling, Adam?

55:43.514 --> 55:44.863
You sleeping all right?

55:49.041 --> 55:50.738
Any more lucid
dreams or nightmares?

55:50.869 --> 55:53.741
It felt real to me, OK?

55:53.872 --> 55:55.526
I could see out of both eyes.

55:55.656 --> 55:56.527
And then--

55:56.657 --> 55:58.877
Adam, we've been over this.

55:59.007 --> 56:01.488
The operation was
a complete success.

56:01.619 --> 56:03.142
No complications, and
so far, no setbacks.

56:03.272 --> 56:03.751
OK?

56:08.582 --> 56:10.976
How are you
adjusting sight-wise?

56:14.327 --> 56:15.241
I'm still getting used to it.

56:21.029 --> 56:24.598
Dr. Markonen told me to passon that your wife called again.

56:24.729 --> 56:29.081
She apologized for the delayand said she'll be here soon.

56:29.211 --> 56:31.344
ADAM : They'relying to you, of course.

56:31.475 --> 56:34.869
You know, it's
OK to feel anxious.

56:35.000 --> 56:36.218
About seeing your wife.

56:36.349 --> 56:37.698
ADAM : They
think you're weak.

56:37.829 --> 56:40.179
LESLIE: You've just
had major surgery.

56:40.309 --> 56:44.052
It's a big adjustment
for everyone.

56:44.183 --> 56:49.797
With a loss of health, it's notuncommon to feel a betrayal.

56:49.928 --> 56:52.800
ADAM : Too
weak to know the truth.

56:52.931 --> 56:54.411
LESLIE: That your own bodyis turning against you.

56:57.805 --> 57:01.200
It's not unusual to feel--

57:01.330 --> 57:03.855
well, that you're
not really whole.

57:03.985 --> 57:05.030
That there's something missing.

57:05.160 --> 57:06.335
Oh, there's
something missing--

57:06.466 --> 57:07.511
doctor.

57:07.641 --> 57:11.123
That's for sure-- my daughter.

57:11.253 --> 57:13.125
My wife.

57:13.255 --> 57:15.214
My sight.

57:15.344 --> 57:18.435
ADAM : But Iknow you're ready to see.

57:18.565 --> 57:21.481
ADAM: How long is
this going to go on?

57:21.612 --> 57:23.744
Did Markonen feed you
that bit about betrayal?

57:23.875 --> 57:25.790
It seems like something
you'd have to experience

57:25.920 --> 57:27.313
in order to articulate.

57:30.098 --> 57:30.969
ADAM : Through me.

57:36.627 --> 57:39.368
Why can't I see my family?

57:39.499 --> 57:40.282
Let go of the door, Adam.

57:40.413 --> 57:41.849
Why can't I see them?

57:41.980 --> 57:42.676
Let go now!

57:59.345 --> 58:01.086
What the fuck?

58:01.216 --> 58:01.695
What?

58:05.307 --> 58:06.526
Can you see me, Adam?

58:10.878 --> 58:12.358
Adam.

58:12.489 --> 58:13.968
Uh, your bandages.

58:14.099 --> 58:15.100
Um, y-- yeah.

58:15.230 --> 58:17.102
I-- I had-- had an itch.

58:17.232 --> 58:18.669
Well, you should
have waited for me.

58:18.799 --> 58:20.584
Well, my patience iswearing a little thin, doc.

58:20.714 --> 58:23.891
But we-- we don't
want it to get infected.

58:24.022 --> 58:26.328
Is that why it
looks like this?

58:26.459 --> 58:27.504
No.

58:27.634 --> 58:30.550
Uh, this is the
latest prosthetic.

58:30.681 --> 58:32.117
And, uh, I know it
takes a little getting

58:32.247 --> 58:33.727
used to, but I promise it's--

58:33.858 --> 58:35.599
it's helping the surroundingtissues heal fas--

58:35.729 --> 58:37.165
It doesn't feel
like a prosthetic.

58:37.296 --> 58:40.473
Will you please
let me look at it?

58:40.604 --> 58:42.606
You don't want to
wait for Dr. Leslie?

58:42.736 --> 58:43.781
No.

58:43.911 --> 58:47.088
Um, I sent her home.

58:47.219 --> 58:50.004
She hasn't been
feeling well lately.

58:50.135 --> 58:50.657
Welcome to the club.

58:54.269 --> 58:56.620
MARKONEN: OK.

58:56.750 --> 58:59.884
Here we go.

59:00.014 --> 59:00.493
OK.

59:03.540 --> 59:07.369
Now the hard part.

59:07.500 --> 59:10.590
ADAM : I
know what you want.

59:10.721 --> 59:11.591
Easy.

59:11.722 --> 59:13.462
D-- did you hear that?

59:13.593 --> 59:15.203
What?

59:15.334 --> 59:15.987
ADAM : I'll takeyou to your wife and daughter.

59:19.294 --> 59:22.602
I know this is veryuncomfortable for you, Adam.

59:22.733 --> 59:25.518
But it's also very important.

59:25.649 --> 59:26.563
Can you please try to relax?

59:33.091 --> 59:36.007
ADAM : An
eye for an eye, Adam.

59:36.137 --> 59:37.225
Very still.

59:37.356 --> 59:38.183
Still, now.

59:38.313 --> 59:39.227
Easy.

59:39.358 --> 59:41.882
Very still, now.

59:42.013 --> 59:44.755
ADAM : Youknow what you have to do.

59:44.885 --> 59:45.886
Easy.

59:46.017 --> 59:46.844
Easy.

59:46.974 --> 59:47.801
How much longer?

59:47.932 --> 59:49.629
Uh, just, uh-- just--

59:49.760 --> 59:50.630
just a moment, please.

59:50.761 --> 59:51.500
It burns.

59:51.631 --> 59:52.153
ADAM : Do it.

59:52.284 --> 59:53.459
Yeah, yeah.

59:53.590 --> 59:54.373
Just take a breath.

59:54.503 --> 59:55.330
Take a breath.

59:55.461 --> 59:56.244
Wow.

59:56.375 --> 59:58.159
ADAM : Do it!

59:58.290 --> 59:59.334
I need a break!

59:59.465 --> 59:59.900
MARKONEN: No.

1:00:00.031 --> 1:00:00.509
Wait!

1:00:00.640 --> 1:00:01.510
I can't.

1:00:01.641 --> 1:00:03.251
Yes, you can, Adam.

1:00:03.382 --> 1:00:04.557
Yes, you can.

1:00:04.688 --> 1:00:06.733
Oh, you are lucky to be alive.

1:00:06.864 --> 1:00:07.734
ADAM : Pay the toll!

1:00:07.865 --> 1:00:08.474
Whoa.

1:00:08.605 --> 1:00:09.301
Whoa.
Adam.

1:00:09.431 --> 1:00:10.215
Adam.
Calm down.

1:00:10.345 --> 1:00:11.346
Calm down.

1:00:11.477 --> 1:00:11.999
You did this to
me, didn't you?

1:00:12.130 --> 1:00:12.826
No.
No.

1:00:12.957 --> 1:00:13.522
I'm sorry.

1:00:13.653 --> 1:00:15.742
I had to see it.

1:00:15.873 --> 1:00:17.135
Who the fuck are you?

1:00:17.265 --> 1:00:18.876
Adam, if you just give me a--

1:00:37.938 --> 1:00:39.244
Mother fucker!

1:00:52.387 --> 1:00:53.954
You know, you've
been given a gift.

1:00:56.696 --> 1:01:00.961
Insights into realitieswe can't even conceive of.

1:01:01.092 --> 1:01:02.833
And what do you do, huh?

1:01:02.963 --> 1:01:03.529
What do you do?

1:01:06.488 --> 1:01:09.578
You succumb to blind rage?

1:01:09.709 --> 1:01:10.275
No.

1:01:10.405 --> 1:01:10.841
No.

1:01:14.453 --> 1:01:17.282
Sorry, Adam.

1:01:17.412 --> 1:01:20.546
You don't deserve it.

1:01:20.677 --> 1:01:21.416
No!

1:01:21.547 --> 1:01:22.026
No!

1:01:22.156 --> 1:01:23.418
No!

1:01:23.549 --> 1:01:24.245
No!

1:01:31.035 --> 1:01:31.688
Don't shoot.
- No, no, no.

1:01:31.818 --> 1:01:32.384
I had to stop him.

1:01:32.514 --> 1:01:33.385
Don't shoot.

1:01:33.515 --> 1:01:33.646
He was going to kill you.

1:01:37.041 --> 1:01:39.347
What do you want from me?

1:01:39.478 --> 1:01:41.436
Adam, please.

1:01:41.567 --> 1:01:44.918
I just want to help.

1:01:45.049 --> 1:01:46.615
Your wife-- she hasn't called.

1:01:46.746 --> 1:01:47.529
She's on the other side.

1:01:47.660 --> 1:01:49.618
Almost everyone is.

1:01:49.749 --> 1:01:50.445
My family, too.

1:01:50.576 --> 1:01:51.577
Other side of what?

1:01:51.708 --> 1:01:55.102
The thing you crashed into.

1:01:55.233 --> 1:01:57.235
We think it's some kind
of doorway or portal.

1:01:57.365 --> 1:01:58.062
Portal to where?

1:01:58.192 --> 1:01:59.541
Where are they?

1:01:59.672 --> 1:02:01.413
We were hoping
you could tell us.

1:02:01.543 --> 1:02:02.762
Me?

1:02:02.893 --> 1:02:04.198
You passed through, Adam.

1:02:04.329 --> 1:02:06.723
And somehow, you made it back--

1:02:06.853 --> 1:02:07.811
with that.

1:02:07.941 --> 1:02:10.596
This?

1:02:10.727 --> 1:02:13.599
But he said that
this is a prosthesis.

1:02:13.730 --> 1:02:16.820
He tried cutting it out
and it started changing,

1:02:16.950 --> 1:02:18.691
and I stopped him.

1:02:18.822 --> 1:02:20.388
He became obsessed,
insisting it was

1:02:20.519 --> 1:02:23.783
some link to the other
side, like a window or--

1:02:23.914 --> 1:02:24.610
Or a mirror.

1:02:28.179 --> 1:02:28.962
Tell me everything you know.

1:02:31.835 --> 1:02:33.140
Follow me.

1:02:33.271 --> 1:02:35.664
Some are convincedthey're extraterrestrial,

1:02:35.795 --> 1:02:38.493
even interdimensional beings.

1:02:38.624 --> 1:02:40.234
Others tend to
get more biblical.

1:02:40.365 --> 1:02:41.627
What do you think?

1:02:41.758 --> 1:02:43.063
There's anintelligence behind them.

1:02:43.194 --> 1:02:44.064
That's all we know for sure.

1:02:46.893 --> 1:02:48.460
And they're not to
be underestimated.

1:02:56.947 --> 1:02:59.297
What is this place?

1:02:59.427 --> 1:03:03.562
We're a VA hospital withsome additional services.

1:03:03.692 --> 1:03:06.130
You mean like a military base?

1:03:06.260 --> 1:03:08.393
Used to be, anyway.

1:03:08.523 --> 1:03:08.959
Ah!

1:03:11.700 --> 1:03:13.180
Keep your eye closed.

1:03:13.311 --> 1:03:15.139
It's only going to
get worse from here.

1:03:30.328 --> 1:03:32.069
Lost a lot of lives
bringing it here.

1:03:32.199 --> 1:03:32.983
Markonen insisted.

1:03:42.862 --> 1:03:44.603
We discovered that
it emits a form

1:03:44.733 --> 1:03:47.432
of high-frequency radiation.

1:03:47.562 --> 1:03:48.607
So we tried
communicating with it.

1:03:50.391 --> 1:03:52.480
What did it say?

1:03:52.611 --> 1:03:55.005
I think it says somethingdifferent for each of us.

1:03:55.135 --> 1:03:57.181
For Markonen, it promisedanswers, insight.

1:04:01.011 --> 1:04:03.056
And then you showed
up with that eye.

1:04:03.187 --> 1:04:04.536
What did it promise you?

1:04:08.627 --> 1:04:11.021
My wife.

1:04:11.151 --> 1:04:11.978
In exchange for what?

1:04:15.677 --> 1:04:16.896
For me?

1:04:17.027 --> 1:04:19.377
Maybe you can save
both our families.

1:04:19.507 --> 1:04:22.641
You're the only one who's beento the other side and back.

1:04:22.771 --> 1:04:24.208
Well, it wasn't free, was it?

1:04:27.124 --> 1:04:30.605
That's a risk I'm
willing to take.

1:04:30.736 --> 1:04:31.171
Are you?

1:04:45.751 --> 1:04:46.621
Good luck.

1:05:05.205 --> 1:05:06.554
How long does this take?

1:05:31.101 --> 1:05:32.972
Oh!

1:05:47.900 --> 1:05:48.379
Oh, no.

1:05:48.509 --> 1:05:49.293
No, no.

1:05:49.423 --> 1:05:51.860
No, no, no, no, no, no!

1:05:51.991 --> 1:05:52.861
Gah!

1:05:52.992 --> 1:05:56.953
Son of a bitch!

1:05:57.083 --> 1:05:57.562
Fuck!

1:06:09.226 --> 1:06:09.966
Fuck it.

1:07:31.134 --> 1:07:32.874
Gah!

1:07:33.005 --> 1:07:33.440
Ow!

1:07:58.639 --> 1:07:59.510
What the fuck?

1:08:17.963 --> 1:08:20.835
Ah!

1:08:20.966 --> 1:08:23.751
CHILD'S VOICE : Daddy!

1:08:23.882 --> 1:08:25.362
Honey?

1:08:25.492 --> 1:08:25.927
Honey!

1:08:42.944 --> 1:08:44.032
Andrea?

1:08:44.163 --> 1:08:46.513
That was my mother's name.

1:08:49.125 --> 1:08:49.951
Who are you?

1:08:53.041 --> 1:08:53.912
Kate?

1:08:54.042 --> 1:08:56.697
How do you know my name?

1:08:56.828 --> 1:08:57.263
No.

1:09:00.745 --> 1:09:02.399
It's-- it's your dad.

1:09:02.529 --> 1:09:03.835
Kate, no!

1:09:03.965 --> 1:09:04.836
Please, no.

1:09:04.966 --> 1:09:05.576
Kate, I have to ask you--

1:09:12.670 --> 1:09:13.497
ADAM 2: Have a seat, Adam.

1:09:19.546 --> 1:09:22.332
Is this some kind of a joke?

1:09:22.462 --> 1:09:24.203
It's funny to you, too.

1:09:26.292 --> 1:09:27.119
Sit down.

1:09:39.349 --> 1:09:40.959
What did you do
to my daughter?

1:09:41.089 --> 1:09:42.265
Nothing.

1:09:42.395 --> 1:09:44.223
But neither did you.

1:09:44.354 --> 1:09:45.920
And look at her--

1:09:46.051 --> 1:09:49.707
happy, healthy, well-adjusted.

1:09:49.837 --> 1:09:51.926
Almost as if she's
better off without you.

1:09:55.060 --> 1:09:56.192
Why are you doing this to me?

1:10:02.285 --> 1:10:04.200
We're well beyond that, Adam.

1:10:04.330 --> 1:10:12.556
Let's think of this as anexperiment-- or an exchange.

1:10:12.686 --> 1:10:15.298
We see the world
through your eyes,

1:10:15.428 --> 1:10:16.908
while you live
happily on our side.

1:10:20.825 --> 1:10:21.608
Andrea.

1:10:21.739 --> 1:10:23.262
Kate.

1:10:23.393 --> 1:10:25.177
Or you could leave us andlet fate take its course.

1:10:34.317 --> 1:10:39.147
It's your choice-- if you'rewilling to pay for it.

1:10:39.278 --> 1:10:43.064
These roads have a
toll, I'm afraid.

1:10:43.195 --> 1:10:45.371
What do you want from me?

1:10:45.502 --> 1:10:48.722
Stay, and give
us the other eye.

1:10:48.853 --> 1:10:52.073
Leave, and we take
back your new eye.

1:10:52.204 --> 1:10:53.771
One or the other.

1:10:53.901 --> 1:10:55.425
You can't have both.

1:10:59.429 --> 1:11:03.520
If I stay, I won't reallysee them again, will I?

1:11:03.650 --> 1:11:05.913
It w-- it won't be real.

1:11:06.044 --> 1:11:08.046
It never really was.

1:11:08.176 --> 1:11:09.134
You just didn't notice.

1:11:11.832 --> 1:11:13.965
But you would be together.

1:11:14.095 --> 1:11:16.184
Happy.

1:11:16.315 --> 1:11:18.099
Isn't that what really matters?

1:11:22.539 --> 1:11:24.976
Adam, close your eyes.

1:11:31.591 --> 1:11:33.419
And open them.

1:11:45.649 --> 1:11:47.128
Welcome home, Adam.

1:11:53.744 --> 1:11:55.049
Your family is waiting for you.

1:11:57.922 --> 1:11:58.618
See their faces.

1:12:02.883 --> 1:12:04.581
Make them safe again.

1:12:08.367 --> 1:12:10.195
Be together forever.

1:12:13.633 --> 1:12:16.810
All that's left now
is to pay the toll.

1:12:16.941 --> 1:12:20.336
An eye for an eye.

1:12:20.466 --> 1:12:21.772
You want me to pay the toll?

1:12:27.604 --> 1:12:28.256
Take them.

1:12:28.387 --> 1:12:29.214
What's he doing?

1:12:29.345 --> 1:12:30.084
No.

1:12:30.215 --> 1:12:30.781
No.

1:12:30.911 --> 1:12:32.130
We had a deal.

1:12:48.451 --> 1:12:51.018
MARKONEN : The mindcan adapt to new realities.

1:12:53.978 --> 1:12:55.762
If you're willing
to pay the toll.

1:13:01.725 --> 1:13:03.422
Honestly, considering
the accident,

1:13:03.553 --> 1:13:05.772
it's a miracle, really.

1:13:05.903 --> 1:13:07.078
He's lucky to be alive.

1:13:07.208 --> 1:13:09.602
No, doctor, thank
you for everything.

1:13:09.733 --> 1:13:12.910
We're so grateful.

1:13:13.040 --> 1:13:15.826
We removed the bandages today.

1:13:15.956 --> 1:13:19.090
Dr. Markonen felt it bestthe wounds be left to breathe

1:13:19.220 --> 1:13:21.266
and heal on their own.

1:13:21.397 --> 1:13:24.269
Are you sure she's going
to be OK with this?

1:13:24.400 --> 1:13:27.794
I just want to
see Daddy's face.

1:13:27.925 --> 1:13:28.404
Yeah.

1:13:31.842 --> 1:13:34.235
Adam.

1:13:34.366 --> 1:13:36.586
Someone's here to see you.

1:13:36.716 --> 1:13:38.152
Honey?

1:13:38.283 --> 1:13:39.502
Oh, sweetie.

1:13:39.632 --> 1:13:40.633
Oh, sweetie.

1:13:40.764 --> 1:13:41.286
Oh!

1:14:32.206 --> 1:14:33.512
JAMES: Where do I
think they're from?

1:14:36.776 --> 1:14:37.821
Hard to say, at the moment.

1:14:42.434 --> 1:14:44.175
They don't have any
masks, it seems.

1:14:46.830 --> 1:14:48.875
But they are there.

1:14:49.006 --> 1:14:50.660
And people have
interacted with them.

1:14:53.401 --> 1:14:54.881
That changes everything
we know about physics.

1:14:58.015 --> 1:15:00.365
ANNA: So many people havelost their loved ones.

1:15:00.496 --> 1:15:03.542
Everyone's been affected.

1:15:03.673 --> 1:15:08.286
But you-- you hope.

1:15:08.416 --> 1:15:11.419
JAMES: We have no
idea what they are.

1:15:11.550 --> 1:15:13.073
And I think it's goingto take a while before we

1:15:13.204 --> 1:15:17.469
have any solid understanding.

1:15:17.600 --> 1:15:21.821
But we m-- we just don't know.

1:15:25.433 --> 1:15:27.218
And that's a little terrifying.

1:15:45.192 --> 1:15:47.630
I've gone over thecalculations again and again.

1:15:47.760 --> 1:15:48.805
And I still can't guaran--

1:15:48.935 --> 1:15:50.415
ANNA: James, we both have.

1:15:50.546 --> 1:15:53.461
JAMES: If the connection
between the two portals

1:15:53.592 --> 1:15:57.640
isn't stable while we're inside,we're, for lack of a better

1:15:57.770 --> 1:16:00.207
term, completely fucked.

1:16:00.338 --> 1:16:01.295
Look, we've done the work.

1:16:01.426 --> 1:16:02.688
We've tracked the patterns.

1:16:02.819 --> 1:16:04.560
Our science is sound.

1:16:04.690 --> 1:16:07.867
Now all we need is
a bit of faith, OK?

1:16:07.998 --> 1:16:12.219
JAMES: Have a little faith.

1:16:12.350 --> 1:16:16.920
Anna, you do know this is aportal we're talking about?

1:16:17.050 --> 1:16:19.487
James, look around us.

1:16:19.618 --> 1:16:21.838
There is nothing left.

1:16:21.968 --> 1:16:22.795
We need to do this now.

1:16:29.323 --> 1:16:29.759
OK.

1:16:32.936 --> 1:16:34.024
Initiating energy burst.

1:17:10.016 --> 1:17:10.495
JAMES: Anna?

1:17:10.626 --> 1:17:11.191
I'm OK.

1:17:18.372 --> 1:17:21.201
It worked.

1:17:21.332 --> 1:17:22.072
It worked!

